{
  "stem": "7546.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "What do you call wooden things that you put together trees-- cut of trees-- and tied together--",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not a barge, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A ferry, like a ferry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A ferry is a boat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It skips my mind right now, but it was a handmade barge made out of trees, and that is the way he crossed people from the German border into the Russian border.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Unfortunately, that was a night-- by the way, where I live here, I have two of my friends that were with me on the same trip.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One of them, two brothers also.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of them went right back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One of them crossed with me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "What happened, the Germans and the Russians were playing patsy at that time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's the only thing I could call it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's either patsy or catch the wolf.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were shooting at the barges of whoever tried to cross the Bug.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it was a very severe winter, and there was already chunks of ice floating in the river.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I had a brother that was 6' 1'.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He was a very tall boy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And while he was standing, whether it was a few bullets from a machine gun or one bullet, he got shot in the head.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the top of his head came off completely, and he just buckled over and went under water.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that friend of ours, a neighbor that lives here too-- we are still friends-- didn't let me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I went to jump in and save him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I happened to be a good swimmer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He didn't let me go.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He says, forget it, he's dead.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I was really in a panic, and I was-- I must have been in very bad shape, because I just listened to him like I was either mesmerized or totally stoned.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
